<%- layout("layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="disability-support-page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8">
        <h1>Accessibility at Wanderlust</h1>
        <p class="lead">We're committed to making travel accessible for everyone</p>
        
        <h2>Digital accessibility at Wanderlust</h2>
        
        <h3>How we work</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Incorporating digital accessibility best practices into our design and engineering processes</li>
          <li>Providing ongoing accessibility training and resources to our employees</li>
          <li>Engaging internal and external quality assurance testers</li>
          <li>Maintaining a cross-functional team dedicated to monitoring and addressing digital accessibility issues across our website and applications</li>
          <li>Training our customer support agents on digital accessibility issues</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Feedback</h3>
        <p>We value your feedback on accessibility. If you encounter any accessibility issues, please reach out to us:</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:accessibility@wanderlust.com" class="btn-link">accessibility@wanderlust.com</a></p>
        <p><a href="/helpcenter" class="btn-link">Wanderlust Community Support →</a></p>

        <h2>Our digital access specifications</h2>
        <p>We test our platform with the following assistive technologies:</p>
        
        <div class="spec-card">
          <h3>Screen readers</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>VoiceOver for macOS (Safari browser)</li>
            <li>VoiceOver for iOS (Safari browser and native app)</li>
            <li>TalkBack for Android (Chrome browser and native app)</li>
            <li>JAWS with Microsoft Edge</li>
            <li>NVDA with Mozilla Firefox</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="spec-card">
          <h3>Keyboard navigation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Desktop Web with Windows</li>
            <li>Desktop Web with macOS</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="spec-card">
          <h3>Font magnification</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Android mobile OS</li>
            <li>Dynamic type: iOS mobile OS</li>
            <li>Adjustable font sizes: Web (Chrome for Desktop, Safari for iOS)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="spec-card">
          <h3>Testing devices</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>The oldest iOS phone tested is iPhone 7</li>
            <li>Android testing devices include Google and Samsung (Pixel 3 and Galaxy S8 are the oldest models)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Accessibility features we support</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Screen reader support</li>
          <li>Colour contrast minimums</li>
          <li>Responsive web design</li>
          <li>Font magnification, dynamic type, adjustable font size</li>
          <li>Open captions for video content</li>
          <li>Image descriptions for Wanderlust-created content</li>
          <li>Keyboard shortcuts on web</li>
          <li>Map zoom controls</li>
          <li>Map pan controls</li>
          <li>Reduced motion settings</li>
          <li>Prevent video autoplay</li>
          <li>Load more option (versus infinite scroll)</li>
          <li>Sound off by default</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Known limitations</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Listing images, customer profile photos and other uploaded images may not have descriptions</li>
          <li>Content that appears on Wanderlust platforms via third-party vendors may not be accessible</li>
          <li>We do not test our platform compatibility on tablets</li>
          <li>We do not test keyboard access on native mobile applications or Braille display</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>We're here to help</h2>
        <div class="help-links">
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Stays with accessibility features →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Experiences with accessibility features →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Access providers and related experiences policies →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Service animal policies →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Hosting guests with accessibility needs →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Welcoming guests with accessibility needs →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Adding accessibility features to stays listings →</a>
          <a href="#" class="help-link">Adding accessibility features to experiences listings →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <h3>Quick links</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar-links">
            <li><a href="#">Accessibility features search</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Service animal policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Hosting with accessibility</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Report an accessibility issue</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Need help?</h3>
          <p>If you have questions about accessibility or need assistance, our team is here to help.</p>
          <a href="/helpcenter" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-block">Contact Support</a>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Standards we follow</h3>
          <p>We strive to meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards for web accessibility.</p>
          <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/" target="_blank" class="btn-link">Learn about WCAG 2.1 →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
